# Clerk Billing

Subscriptions and payments use **Clerk Billing** (B2C). Billing is beta; follow [Clerk pinning guidance](https://clerk.com/docs/pinning.md) for stable SDK/`clerk-js` versions.

## Catalog (use these exact keys)

**Plans**

- `free_user`
- `pro`

**Features (entitlements)**

- `3_desk_limit`
- `unlimited_desks`
- `ai_flashcard_generation`

## Plan → feature mapping (authoritative)

- **`free_user`**: `3_desk_limit` (does **not** include `unlimited_desks` or `ai_flashcard_generation`).
- **`pro`**: `unlimited_desks`, `ai_flashcard_generation`.

Mirror this mapping in the [Clerk Dashboard](https://dashboard.clerk.com/~/billing/plans) so `has({ feature: "..." })` matches product rules. Plans managed in Clerk do not sync with Stripe products; Stripe is used for payment processing only.

## Non-negotiable key usage

- Use these keys **exactly as-is** in code and Dashboard config (case-sensitive):
  - plans: `free_user`, `pro`
  - features: `3_desk_limit`, `unlimited_desks`, `ai_flashcard_generation`
- Do not translate, rename, or alias plan/feature keys in checks.

## Pricing UI

Prefer a dedicated route that renders `<PricingTable />` from `@clerk/nextjs` (see [PricingTable docs](https://clerk.com/docs/nextjs/reference/components/billing/pricing-table.md)).

```tsx
import { PricingTable } from "@clerk/nextjs";

export default function PricingPage() {
  return (
    <div style={{ maxWidth: "800px", margin: "0 auto", padding: "0 1rem" }}>
      <PricingTable />
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Gating access (recommended patterns)

Use **Plan** or **Feature** checks—pick the smallest unit that matches the product rule (e.g. cap desks by feature, not by duplicating plan checks everywhere).

### Server Components / Server Actions / Route Handlers

Use `has()` from the Clerk auth object:

```typescript
import { auth } from "@clerk/nextjs/server";

export default async function Example() {
  const { has } = await auth();

  const isPro = has({ plan: "pro" });
  const canUseAi = has({ feature: "ai_flashcard_generation" });

  if (!canUseAi) {
    return <p>Upgrade to use AI flashcard generation.</p>;
  }
  // ...
}
```

Reference: [`has()`](https://clerk.com/docs/reference/backend/types/auth-object.md#has), [auth object](https://clerk.com/docs/reference/backend/types/auth-object.md).

### Client Components

Use `<Show>` from `@clerk/nextjs` with `when={{ plan: "..." }}` or `when={{ feature: "..." }}` and a `fallback` when access is missing.

```tsx
import { Show } from "@clerk/nextjs";

export default function ProtectedContent() {
  return (
    <Show
      when={{ feature: "ai_flashcard_generation" }}
      fallback={<p>Upgrade to Pro to use AI flashcard generation.</p>}
    >
      <p>AI tools are available.</p>
    </Show>
  );
}
```

Reference: [`<Show>`](https://clerk.com/docs/nextjs/reference/components/control/show.md).

## Security

**Enforcement belongs on the server.** Client-only `<Show>` improves UX; do not rely on hiding UI as authorization. For mutations and sensitive data, re-check entitlements in Server Actions or Route Handlers (and keep data isolation per `clerk-auth-data-isolation.mdc`).
